            <ol class="ol ol safety" id="smoke_detector___troubleshooting__safety_of5_dxj_gdb">
                
                <li class="li li safecond">
                    <div class="note note"><span class="notetitle">Note:</span> The LED on the detector head of both the ionization and photoelectric
                        models will flash while the unit is in standby mode. The LED on the smoke
                        detector head will be permanently illuminated when smoke is detected and the
                        head is in alarm.</div>

                    <div class="note note"><span class="notetitle">Note:</span> Do not use chemicals or non-conforming air to clean the detector head
                        housing as this could contaminate the detector head and damage the
                        casing.</div>

                </li>

            </ol>

        </div>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">To determine the correct operation of the smoke detector, ensure the green
                    pilot LED is illuminated.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">If the smoke detector goes off at random, make sure the cover is not dusty by
                    taking it of and cleaning it.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Using smoke canister, test the smoke detector to ensure normal operation.</span>
            </li>
</ol>

